.TH JARVIS 1 "March 2026" "0.1.0" "Jarvis User Manual"
.SH NAME
jarvis \- Local AI Assistant for Coding, Research, and Knowledge Management
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jarvis
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fICOMMAND\fR]
.br
.B jarvis
'\fINATURAL LANGUAGE PROMPT\fR'
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jarvis
is a powerful local AI agent designed for NixOS. It orchestrates multiple LLMs (Qwen3, Mistral, Qwen2.5-Coder) via Ollama to perform complex coding tasks, technical research, and automated knowledge ingestion.
.br
It features a hierarchical 3-Layer Knowledge Architecture that prioritizes local documentation over web searches to achieve high accuracy and sub-2.5 minute latencies on local CPU hardware.
.SH COMMANDS AND INTERNAL MECHANISMS
.TP
.B status
Displays the health of all Jarvis background services and Ollama models.
.br
\fBMechanism:\fR Executes \fCsystemctl --user is-active\fR on the systemd units (e.g., \fCjarvis-health-monitor\fR, \fCjarvis-coding-agent\fR) and polls the Ollama REST API to verify loaded models. Note: \fCjarvis-ingest\fR is now deprecated in favor of explicit commands.
.TP
.B start / stop
Starts or stops all background daemon services.
.br
\fBMechanism:\fR Wraps \fCsystemctl --user start/stop\fR for Jarvis targets.
.TP
.B pause / resume
Temporarily suspends or continues AI inference.
.br
\fBMechanism:\fR Sends \fBSIGSTOP\fR or \fBSIGCONT\fR to the Ollama process, freezing memory state while freeing CPU.
.TP
.B inbox [process \fIID\fR]
Manages the researcher's queue. If \fBprocess\fR is called with an \fIID\fR, Jarvis retrieves the document and performs an isolated ingestion.
.br
\fBMechanism:\fR Interfaces via \fBKnowledgeManager\fR with SQLite \fCknowledge.db\fR. Ingestion creates a unique category (\fCpdf_doc_<ID>\fR) in Layer 3 to prevent domain mixing.
.TP
.B learn \fIURL/FILE\fR [--layer \fI1-3\fR] [--category \fINAME\fR]
Explicitly ingests a local file (PDF, MD, DOCX) or a URL into the knowledge base.
.br
\fBMechanism:\fR Local PDFs are processed via \fBMinerU\fR (magic-pdf) for high-fidelity markdown extraction before being chunked and embedded into the 3-Layer knowledge store (\fBchunks\fR table).
.TP
.B knowledge [list|summary]
Inspects knowledge base entries. \fBlist\fR shows all chunks; \fBsummary\fR provides a high-level view of trained languages and tools.
.TP
.B training
Displays a status grid of language competency (✓/✗) across the 3-Layer knowledge architecture.
.TP
.B config nvim|nixos "\fITASK\fR"
Enters a specialized configuration editing mode for Neovim (Lua) or NixOS (Nix modules). 
.br
\fBMechanism:\fR Launches the \fBagent_loop.py\fR with context-specific roles (\fCnvim_config\fR or \fCnixos_config\fR) and deep reference to the respective indexed codebases.
.TP
.B index [\fIDIR\fR] --category \fINAME\fR
Indexes a local codebase for the **Coding Agent**.
.br
\fBMechanism:\fR Scans the directory and stores file contents in the \fBchunks\fR table (Layer 2) under the specified category.
.TP
.B query "\fIQUESTION\fR" [--category \fINAME\fR]
Performs a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) query against the knowledge base.
.br
\fBMechanism:\fR Executes the \fBquery_knowledge\fR pipeline. It retrieves relevant context from the \fBchunks\fR table using lexical search and generates an answer using the local LLM.
.TP
.B dashboard
Opens the recompiled Rust TUI (\fCjarvis-monitor\fR) with optimized contrast and precise task labeling for real-time monitoring of active research and ingestion tasks.
.TP
.B thumbs-up / thumbs-down
Provides feedback for the daily optimizer.
.TP
.B identity "\fIMESSAGE\fR"
Queries Jarvis about his own name, version, and capabilities.
.br
\fBMechanism:\fR Performs a RAG query on the \fCidentity\fR category in Layer 1.
.TP
.B self_improve "\fITASK\fR"
Initiates an autonomous loop for Jarvis to improve his own codebase or documentation.
.br
\fBMechanism:\fR Launches the \fBagent_loop.py\fR orchestrator with the \fCcoding\fR role.
.TP
.B user_profile "\fIPREFERENCE/PLAN\fR"
Manages user-specific preferences and long-term planning data.
.br
\fBMechanism:\fR Stores input in the \fCuser_profile\fR category of the knowledge base.
.TP
.B ingest_materials "\fITOPIC\fR"
Researches coding materials, converts multi-format documents, and indexes them by programming language.
.br
\fBMechanism:\fR Orchestrates \fCresearch_agent.py\fR, \fCdoc_converter.py\fR (MinerU), and \fCdoc_learner.py\fR. Monitoring wait loop at \fC~/Downloads/JarvisMaterials\fR.
.SH DETERMINISTIC EXECUTION
To ensure reliability, Jarvis core subcommands (\fBstatus\fR, \fBstart\fR, \fBstop\fR, \fBpause\fR, \fBresume\fR, \fBlearn\fR, \fBindex\fR, \fBknowledge\fR, \fBinbox\fR, \fBdashboard\fR) \fBbypass\fR the natural language intent classifier. They execute immediately based on parsed arguments.
.SH NATURAL LANGUAGE ROUTING MECHANISM
When a free-text prompt is provided:
.IP 1.
The \fBjarvis.py\fR entrypoint parses the arguments and passes the string to the \fCclassify_intent\fR function.
.IP 2.
A fast intent classification model (Qwen 7B) or identity-layer RAG fallback classifies the prompt into an intent (\fBlearn\fR, \fBcode\fR, \fBresearch\fR, \fBidentity\fR, \fBself_improve\fR, \fBuser_profile\fR, \fBingest_materials\fR).
.IP 3.
The \fBroute_intent\fR function dispatches the prompt, performing safety checks for high-risk operations (modifying indexes or identity) which require explicit user confirmation (y/N).
.IP 4.
The prompt is passed to the specialized pipeline (e.g., \fCcoding_agent.py\fR, \fCmaterial_ingestor.py\fR).
.SH HIERARCHICAL KNOWLEDGE PIPELINE (RAG)
Jarvis fetches context using a 3-Layer local structure before hitting the LLM:
.IP \(bu 2
\fBLayer 1 (Language)\fR: Core syntax and standard library docs.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBLayer 2 (Domain)\fR: Framework-specific guides and community docs.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBLayer 3 (Theory)\fR: Deep conceptual books and problem-class theory.
.br
\fBMechanism:\fR
When a task dictates domain knowledge (e.g., 'rewrite in Rust'), the \fBKnowledgeManager\fR searches \fCknowledge.db\fR using cosine similarity against the prompt's embedding. High-scoring chunks from the relevant layers are retrieved, formatted, and forcefully injected into the LLM system prompt under a \fI[LOCAL KNOWLEDGE]\fR XML block to prevent hallucinations.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /THE_VAULT/jarvis/
Base directory for all Jarvis data and logic.
.TP
.I /THE_VAULT/jarvis/data/knowledge.db
SQLite database for the 3-Layer Knowledge Base and Embeddings.
.TP
.I /THE_VAULT/jarvis/logs/events.db
Daily activity log and episodic memory.
